s Antilles</option>\r\n            <option value="New Caledonia">New Caledonia</option>\r\n            <option value="New Zealand">New Zealand</option>\r\n            <option value="Nicaragua">Nicaragua</option>\r\n            <option value="Niger">Niger</option>\r\n            <option value="Nigeria">Nigeria</option>\r\n            <option value="Niue">Niue</option>\r\n            <option value="Norfolk Island">Norfolk Island</option>\r\n            <option value="Northern Mariana Islands">Northern Mariana Islands</option>\r\n            <option value="Norway">Norway</option>\r\n            <option value="Oman">Oman</option>\r\n            <option value="Pakistan">Pakistan</option>\r\n            <option value="Palau">Palau</option>\r\n            <option value="Panama">Panama</option>\r\n            <option value="Papua New Guinea">Papua New Guinea</option>\r\n            <option value="Paraguay">Paraguay</option>\r\n            <option value="Peru">Peru</option>\r\n            <option value="Philippines">Philippines</option>\r\n            <option value="Pitcairn">Pitcairn</option>\r\n            <option value="Poland">Poland</option>\r\n            <option value="Portugal">Portugal</option>\r\n            <option value="Puerto Rico">Puerto Rico</option>\r\n            <option value="Qatar">Qatar</option>\r\n            <option value="Reunion">Reunion</option>\r\n            <option value="Romania">Romania</option>\r\n            <option value="Russian Federation">Russian Federation</option>\r\n            <option value="Rwanda">Rwanda</option>\r\n            <option value="Saint Kitts and Nevis">Saint Kitts and Nevis</option>\r\n            <option value="Saint Lucia">Saint Lucia</option>\r\n            <option value="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines">Saint Vincent and the Grenadines</option>\r\n            <option value="Samoa">Samoa</option>\r\n            <option value="San Marino">San Marino</option>\r\n            <option value="Sao Tome and Principe">Sao Tome and Principe</option>\r\n            <option value="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</option>\r\n            <option value="Senegal">Senegal</option>\r\n            <option value="Seychelles">Seychelles</option>\r\n            <option value="Sierra Leone">Sierra Leone</option>\r\n            <option value="Singapore">Singapore</option>\r\n            <option value="Slovakia">Slovakia (Slovak Republic)</option>\r\n            <option value="Slovenia">Slovenia</option>\r\n            <option value="Solomon Islands">Solomon Islands</option>\r\n            <option value="Somalia">Somalia</option>\r\n            <option value="South Africa">South Africa</option>\r\n            <option value="Spain">Spain</option>\r\n            <option value="Sri Lanka">Sri Lanka</option>\r\n            <option value="St. Helena">St. Helena</option>\r\n            <option value="St. Pierre and Miquelon">St. Pierre and Miquelon</option>\r\n            <option value="Sudan">Sudan</option>\r\n            <option value="Suriname">Suriname</option>\r\n            <option value="Svalbard and Jan Mayen Islands">Svalbard and Jan Mayen Islands</option>\r\n            <option value="Swaziland">Swaziland</option>\r\n            <option value="Sweden">Sweden</option>\r\n            <option value="Switzerland">Switzerland</option>\r\n            <option value="Syrian Arab Republic">Syrian Arab Republic</option>\r\n            <option value="Taiwan">Taiwan</option>\r\n            <option value="Tajikistan">Tajikistan</option>\r\n            <option value="Tanzania">Tanzania, United Republic of</option>\r\n            <option value="Thailand">Thailand</option>\r\n            <option value="Togo">Togo</option>\r\n            <option value="Tokelau">Tokelau</option>\r\n            <option value="Tonga">Tonga</option>\r\n            <option value="Trinidad and Tobago">Trinidad and Tobago</option>\r\n            <option value="Tunisia">Tunisia</option>\r\n            <option value="Turkey">Turkey</option>\r\n            <option value="Turkmenistan">Turkmenistan</option>\r\n            <option value="Turks and Caicos Islands">Turks and Caicos Islands</option>\r\n            <option value="Tuvalu">Tuvalu</option>\r\n            <option value="Uganda">Uganda</option>\r\n            <option value="Ukraine">Ukraine</option>\r\n            <option value="United Arab Emirates">United Arab Emirates</option>\r\n            <option value="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</option>\r\n            <option value="United States">United States</option>\r\n            <option value="Uruguay">Uruguay</option>\r\n            <option value="Uzbekistan">Uzbekistan</option>\r\n            <option value="Vanuatu">Vanuatu</option>\r\n            <option value="Vatican City State">Vatican City State (Holy See)</option>\r\n            <option value="Venezuela">Venezuela</option>\r\n            <option value="Viet Nam">Viet Nam</option>\r\n            <option value="Virgin Islands (British)">Virgin Islands (British)</option>\r\n            <option value="Virgin Islands (U.S.)">Virgin Islands (U.S.)</option>\r\n            <option value="Wallis and Futuna Islands">Wallis and Futuna Islands</option>\r\n            <option value="Western Sahara">Western Sahara</option>\r\n            <option value="Yemen">Yemen</option>\r\n            <option value="Yugoslavia">Yugoslavia</option>\r\n            <option value="Zaire">Zaire</option>\r\n            <option value="Zambia">Zambia</option>\r\n            <option value="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</option>\r\n          </select>\r\n        </label> \r\n        <label for="Telephone"> \r\n          <br />\r\n          <span><strong>* Telephone:</strong></span><br />\r\n          <input type="text" value="" id="Telephone" name="Telephone" size="40" title="Telephone" /> \r\n        </label> \r\n      </fieldset>\r\n      <fieldset>\r\n        <legend>Additional questions</legend> \r\n        <label for="ra"> \r\n          <br />\r\n          <span>* Keywords on <strong>Research Areas or Special Interests </strong>(these will be shown in the workshop information pack as an aid to networking, \r\n            it is important that you complete this section). :</span><br />\r\n          <textarea title="Your Research Areas or Special Interests " rows="3" cols="51" id="ra" name="ra">\r\n          </textarea>\r\n        </label> \r\n        <label for="sr"> \r\n          <br />\r\n          <span>In addition, do you have any <strong>special requirements</strong>?</span><br />\r\n          <textarea title="Special Requirements, eg wheelchair user or vegetarian" rows="3" cols="51" id="sr" name="sr">\r\n          </textarea>\r\n        </label> \r\n      </fieldset>\r\n      <fieldset>\r\n        <legend>Privacy policy</legend> \r\n        <p>We will use the information you provide only for the specific purpose for which \r\n          you have given it, \r\n          and in accordance with our Data Protection Policy. We will not disclose any such \r\n          personal information \r\n          to a third party without your prior consent. The information you have provided \r\n          here will be printed in\r\n          the workshop park.</p>\r\n        <br />\r\n        <label><input type="checkbox" checked="checked" id="privacy" name="privacy" /> \r\n          I have read and agree to the SPARC privacy policy.\r\n        </label> \r\n      </fieldset>\r\n      <input type="hidden" name="referer" id="referer" value="" /> \r\n      <input type="submit" id="submit" name="submit" value="Submit" title="Submit your Registration" /> \r\n      <input type="reset" value="Reset Form" class="reset" title="Clear Form" /> \r\n    </form>\r\n    <h2>Directions</h2>\r\n    <p>Map: <a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps">http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps</a></p>\r\n    <p>Directions: Travel directions and detailed travel maps to the Holywell Park, \r\n      Loughborough University.<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps/">http://www.welcometoimago.com/contact/location/maps/</a> </p>\r\n    <p>The campus map shows how to find Holywell Park on Loughborough University campus:<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.lboro.ac.uk/about/map/pages/map-full.html">http://www.lboro.ac.uk/about/map/pages/map-full.html</a> \r\n      and a pdf downloadable version:<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/pdf/imago-area-map.pdf">http://www.welcometoimago.com/pdf/imago-area-map.pdf</a></p>\r\n    <p>By Road: From M1 (Junction 23) or the A6, follow the signs to the University</p>\r\n    <p>By Rail: 90 minutes from London St Pancras. Approximately 10 minutes by taxi or \r\n      bus from Loughborough train station.<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.midlandmainline.com/">http://www.midlandmainline.com/</a> </p>\r\n    <p>By Bus: A University Shuttle bus, operated by Kinchbus travels between the \r\n      University and Loughborough''s train station daily.<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.kinchbus.co.uk/kinchbus.html">http://www.kinchbus.co.uk/kinchbus.html</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.trentbuses.co.uk/timetables">http://www.trentbuses.co.uk/timetables</a><br />\r\n      Telephone: 01509 816161</p>\r\n    <p>By Air: 8 miles from East Midlands Airport and convenient for Birmingham Airport \r\n      (M42).<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.eastmidlandsairport.com">http://www.eastmidlandsairport.com</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.bhx.co.uk">http://www.bhx.co.uk</a></p>\r\n    <p>On campus accommodation is available for a reasonable price at Burleigh Court, \r\n      Loughborough University. If you need this, you are encouraged<br />\r\n      to book accommodation directly with Burleigh Court, please follow the link<br />\r\n      <a href="http://www.welcometoimago.com/accommodation/">http://www.welcometoimago.com/accommodation/</a></p>\r\n  </article> \r\n</div>\r\n', '2010-11-04 12:00', 1, 0),
(13, 4, 'Conferences', 'get-involved/conferences.html', '* [Designing Inclusive Interactions](http://www-edc.eng.cam.ac.uk/cwuaat/index.html), The 5th Cambridge Workshop on Universal Access (UA) and Assistive Technology (AT) : CWUAAT 2010\r\nFitzwilliam College, University of Cambridge. Reflects the need to explore the issues and practicalities of design that is intended to extend our active future lives. , Cambridge, 23 - 25 March 2010\r\n            \r\n* [12th International Conference on Mobility and Transport for Elderly and Disabled Persons (TRANSED 2010)](http://www.transed2010.hk/front/home2.html%20for), 1 - 4 June 2010 \r\n\r\n* [Better healthcare through better infrastructure](http://www.haciric.org/Portals/36/Conferences/Call.pdf), This event aims to bring together researchers and practitioners from across disciplines and countries to focus on key challenges in the provision of healthcare infrastructure for the 21st century.\r\nEdinburgh, 22 - 24 September 2010', '2010-11-04 12:00', 2, 1),
(14, 5, 'Site Accessibility', 'help/accessibility.html', 'This site has been created with accessibility in mind. All text is displayed in easy-to-read font, with simple colour schemes and layouts to enhance legibility. However, should you experience any problems with this website you can contact our accessibility expert at <accessibility@kt-equal.org.uk>.\r\n', '2010-11-04 12:00', 1, 1),
(15, 5, 'Site Map', 'help/site-map.html', 'A simplified layout of the site.\r\n\r\n## News\r\n\r\n* [Latest News](home/news.html)\r\n* [News Archive](home/archive.html)\r\n\r\n## Info\r\n\r\n* [What is KT-EQUAL](about-us/kt-equal.html)\r\n* [What are SPARC, EPSRC and BBSRC](about-us/sparc-epsrc-bbsrc.html)\r\n* [Who are the main people involved?](about-us/main-people-involved.html)\r\n* [Contact Us](about-us/other-contact-information.html)\r\n\r\n## Projects\r\n\r\n* [KT-EQUAL](projects/kt-equal.html)\r\n* [Other](projects/other.html)\r\n\r\n## Community\r\n\r\n* [Workshops](get-involved/workshops.html)\r\n* [Conferences](get-involved/conferences.html)\r\n* [Forum](forum)\r\n\r\n## Help\r\n\r\n* [Accessibility](help/accessibility.html)\r\n* [Queries & FAQ](help/queries.html)\r\n', '2010-11-04 12:00', 2, 1),
(16, 5, 'Queries and FAQ', 'help/queries.html', '## Queries\r\n\r\nAll queries about the site should be directed at the webmaster <webmaster@kt-equal.org.uk>\r\n\r\n## Frequently Asked Questions\r\n\r\n### What do KT-EQUAL actually do?\r\n\r\nSee [here](about-us/kt-equal.html).\r\n\r\n### How do I get involved in KT-EQUAL?\r\n\r\nGet in contact with one of our representatives, the details of which are available [here](about-us/other-contact-information.html).\r\n\r\n### When did your site start looking so awesome?\r\n\r\nSince James started working on it because he is a champ.', '2010-11-04 12:00', 3, 1),
(17, 4, 'Forum', 'forum/', '', '2010-11-04 12:00', 6, 1);
INSERT INTO sections (id, title, name, image, introduction, "order") VALUES
(1, 'Home', 'home', 'cnt/img/home.jpg', '# Some shit about this section\r\n\r\nMaybe a paragraph about helping old people.\r\n\r\n* Bullet points\r\n* Bullet points\r\n* Bullet points\r\n\r\nLook how amazingly large this text is and this is good because people can read it. Especially the clients of our site.\r\n', 1),
(2, 'About Us', 'about-us', 'cnt/img/about-us.jpg', '# About Us\r\n\r\nThis section of the site is designed to provide you with information about what KT-EQUAL, SPARC, and other associated projects and research, actually are.\r\n\r\nFurthermore you can find background on the KT-EQUAL team and contact information for them.', 2),
(3, 'Projects', 'projects', 'cnt/img/projects.jpg', 'This part of the site is pretty much broken.', 3),
(4, 'Get Involved', 'get-involved', 'cnt/img/get-involved.jpg', '# Getting Involved\r\n\r\nOne of the best ways to help KT-EQUAL is to get involved by doing several things:\r\n\r\n* **Workshops** These provide invaluable training on the latest in ageing technology.\r\n* **Conferences** Listen to our speakers who have a broad range of skills and bring to the table a great deal of experience.\r\n* **Forum** Have your say! Our forum is easy to sign up to and use.', 4),
(5, 'Help', 'help', 'cnt/img/help.jpg', '# Help\r\n\r\nIf you need help using the site or have questions that need answering, this is the section you are looking for.', 5);
